## shadcn-svelte

### Installation

Components are installed using the CLI:

```bash
npx shadcn-ui@latest add [component-name]
```

Components are installed to `src/lib/components/ui/` based on `components.json` configuration.

### Configuration

The `components.json` file configures:

- Tailwind CSS location
- Component aliases (`$lib/components/ui`)
- TypeScript support
- Registry URL

### Using Components

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import { Button } from '$lib/components/ui/button';
	import { Input } from '$lib/components/ui/input';
</script>

<Button>Click me</Button>
<Input placeholder="Enter text..." />
```

### Component Variants

Most shadcn-svelte components support variants:

```svelte
<script>
	import { Button } from '$lib/components/ui/button';
</script>

<Button variant="default">Default</Button>
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<Button variant="outline">Outline</Button>
<Button variant="ghost">Ghost</Button>
```

### Form Components with Remote Functions

Use shadcn-svelte components with remote functions:

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import { createPost } from './data.remote';
	import { Input } from '$lib/components/ui/input';
	import { Button } from '$lib/components/ui/button';
	import { Label } from '$lib/components/ui/label';

	let title = $state('');
	let content = $state('');
	let loading = $state(false);

	async function handleSubmit() {
		loading = true;
		try {
			await createPost({ title, content });
			title = '';
			content = '';
		} finally {
			loading = false;
		}
	}
</script>

<form
	onsubmit={(e) => {
		e.preventDefault();
		handleSubmit();
	}}
>
	<Label for="title">Title</Label>
	<Input id="title" bind:value={title} />

	<Label for="content">Content</Label>
	<Input id="content" bind:value={content} />

	<Button type="submit" disabled={loading}>
		{loading ? 'Submitting...' : 'Submit'}
	</Button>
</form>
```

### Best Practices

1. **Import from aliases** - Use `$lib/components/ui` paths
2. **Customize components** - Edit component files directly (they're yours)
3. **Use TypeScript** - Components are fully typed
4. **Follow accessibility** - Components follow ARIA patterns
5. **Combine with Tailwind** - Use Tailwind utilities for styling
6. **Check documentation** - Visit [shadcn-svelte.com](https://www.shadcn-svelte.com) for component docs

### Common Components

- **Button** - `$lib/components/ui/button`
- **Input** - `$lib/components/ui/input`
- **Label** - `$lib/components/ui/label`
- **Card** - `$lib/components/ui/card`
- **Dialog** - `$lib/components/ui/dialog`
- **Select** - `$lib/components/ui/select`
- **Table** - `$lib/components/ui/table`

