## General Practices

### TypeScript

- Use TypeScript throughout the codebase
- Define types explicitly when needed
- Use type inference from Drizzle schemas
- Export types from schema files

### File Organization

```
src/
├── lib/
│   ├── components/
│   │   └── ui/          # shadcn-svelte components
│   ├── i18n/
│   │   ├── index.svelte.ts  # Translation function (t)
│   │   └── translations.json # Fallback translations
│   ├── server/
│   │   ├── auth.ts      # Authentication utilities
│   │   ├── translations.ts  # Load translations from DB
│   │   └── db/
│   │       ├── index.ts # Database connection
│   │       └── schema.ts # Drizzle schemas
│   └── utils.ts         # Shared utilities
└── routes/
    └── [tenant]/   # Language parameter route
        ├── +layout.server.ts  # Load translations
        ├── +layout.svelte    # Root layout
        └── [route]/
            ├── +page.svelte      # Component
            ├── +page.server.ts   # Load function only (no actions)
            └── data.remote.ts     # Remote functions (queries & commands)
```

### Environment Variables

- Use `$env/dynamic/private` for server-side env vars
- Use `$env/dynamic/public` for client-side env vars
- Always validate env vars exist before use

### Error Handling

- Use SvelteKit's `error()` helper for page errors
- Handle validation errors in remote functions
- Throw errors from remote functions - they'll be caught by components
- Don't expose sensitive information in errors
- Use try-catch in components when calling remote functions

### Code Style

- Use Prettier for formatting
- Use ESLint for linting
- Follow Svelte 5 runes patterns
- Use async/await over promises where possible

### Testing

- Write tests for critical business logic
- Test authentication flows
- Test database operations
- Test remote function calls and error handling

### Security

- Always validate user input
- Use parameterized queries (Drizzle handles this)
- Hash passwords with Argon2
- Use secure session tokens
- Set appropriate cookie flags
- Protect sensitive routes

